wal from PD", "bbox": [45.5, 368.3, 183.7, 379.9]}, {"text": "Dialysis failure/UF failure, n (%) 4 (20.0) 7 (70.0) 0.015 *", "bbox": [55.6, 384.0, 726.3, 395.9]}, {"text": "Prevention of EPS, n (%) 16 (80.0) 3 (30.0)", "bbox": [55.6, 399.9, 623.9, 411.4]}, {"text": "Pathological factors", "bbox": [45.5, 415.6, 132.7, 427.2]}, {"text": "Thickness of peritoneal membrane (μm) 336.2 (262.79–455.75) 550.5 (227.77–750.00) 0.202 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 431.4, 726.3, 443.0]}, {"text": "CD68-positive cells (number/mm) 13.6 (4.21–20.70) 8.6 (0.56–15.42) 0.312 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 447.2, 726.3, 458.8]}, {"text": "Presence of mesothelial cells (grade) 1.0 (0.0–3.0) 1.0 (0.0–3.0) 0.591 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 463.0, 726.3, 474.6]}, {"text": "New membrane formation (grade) 0.0 (0.0–2.0) 1.5 (0.0–2.5) 0.306 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 478.8, 726.3, 490.3]}, {"text": "D2-40 expression (grade) 1.0 (0.0–2.0) 0.5 (0.0–1.5) 0.737 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 494.6, 726.3, 506.1]}, {"text": "CD31 negative vessels, positive case (%) 7 (35.0) 5 (50.0) 0.461 *", "bbox": [45.5, 510.2, 726.3, 522.2]}, {"text": "Ratio of luminal diameter to vessel diameter (L/V ratio) 0.6 (0.43–0.61) 0.3 (0.26–0.43) 0.002 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 526.1, 726.3, 537.7]}, {"text": "Fibrin deposition, positive case (%) 2 (10.0) 5 (50.0) 0.026 *", "bbox": [45.5, 541.8, 726.3, 553.8]}, {"text": "Perivascular bleeding, positive case (%) 2 (10.0) 2 (20.0) 0.584 *", "bbox": [45.5, 557.6, 726.3, 569.6]}, {"text": "AGEs score (grade) 2.0 (1.5–2.5) 2.8 (1.5–3.0) 0.203 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 573.5, 726.3, 585.0]}, {"text": "Collagen volume fraction (%) 18.4 (11.50–24.20) 30.9 (25.50–48.00) 0.031 ‡", "bbox": [45.5, 589.3, 726.3, 600.8]}, {"text": "EPS, encapsulating peritoneal sclerosis; PD, peritoneal dialysis; AGEs, advanced glycation end-products; D2-40 is the same as podoplanin.", "bbox": [45.5, 613.5, 664.3, 625.1]}, {"text": "*n (%), Fisher's exact test;", "bbox": [45.5, 628.6, 163.3, 640.6]}, {"text": "† mean±SD, Student’s t-test;", "bbox": [45.5, 642.9, 171.7, 655.5]}, {"text": "‡ median (IQR), Mann-Whitney's U-test", "bbox": [45.5, 658.1, 218.4, 670.6]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0154644.t003", "bbox": [45.5, 681.9, 186.2, 693.2]}, {"text": "treatment [2,4–6], a risk factor for EPS, exacerbates damage to the vascular endothelial cells by", "bbox": [252.5, 719.3, 723.3, 733.2]}, {"text": "absorption of large amounts of PD solution. These clinical factors are thus often associated", "bbox": [252.5, 735.7, 704.4, 749.6]}, {"text": "with the occurrence of EPS.", "bbox": [252.5, 752.1, 390.0, 766.1]}, {"text": "In contrast to glucose-based acidic PD solution, acidic icodextrin solution was not associ-", "bbox": [267.6, 768.5, 713.1, 782.5]}, {"text": "ated with the occurrence of EPS (Tables 1–4). Icodextrin has been reported to be absorbed", "bbox": [252.5, 784.9, 701.9, 798.9]}, {"text": "mainly through lymphatic vessels from the peritoneal cavity because of the large size of the", "bbox": [252.5, 801.3, 704.7, 815.3]}, {"text": "molecule [49]. In this regard, the impact of damage to vascular endothelial cells may be lower", "bbox": [252.5, 817.8, 716.8, 831.7]}, {"text": "using an acidic icodextrin solution than an acidic glucose-based solution, which can be", "bbox": [252.5, 834.2, 684.5, 848.1]}, {"text": "absorbed via the capillaries. In addition, vasculopathy has been reported to be less severe in", "bbox": [252.5, 850.6, 706.1, 864.5]}, {"text": "patients treated with pH-neutral solution than in patients who undergo treatment with an", "bbox": [252.5, 867.0, 700.7, 881.0]}, {"text": "acidic solution [32,50]. Based on these findings, we conclude that vascular endothelial injury", "bbox": [252.5, 883.4, 712.6, 897.4]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0154644 April 27, 2016 11 / 17", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}